CompanyDescription.label: Company Description
CompanyDescription.value: JBS N.V. is a Netherlands-based global food company and the publicly listed parent of JBS S.A., one of the world's largest protein producers. The company operates in the beef, pork, poultry, and prepared foods sectors, with a portfolio that includes globally recognized brands such as Seara, Swift, Pilgrim's Moy Park, and Primo. Following a corporate restructuring completed in 2025, JBS N.V. became the holding company for the JBS Group's global operations, consolidating its structure and improving access to international capital markets. JBS N.V. is listed on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE: JBS) and has Brazilian Depositary Receipts (BDRs) trading on B3 (JBSS32). With more than 270,000 employees and operations across North America, South America, Europe, and Asia-Pacific, JBS N.V. exports to over 190 countries. The company maintains a vertically integrated supply chain and focuses on food safety, sustainability, and innovation in value-added food products.
